Ing '''Tibet''' ({{bo|t=བོད་|w=bod}} ; [[IPA]]: pʰø̀ʔ; {{zh-c|c=西藏}}) metung yang [[:en:Tibetan Plateau|labuad a matas a kapatagan]] king [[Asia]], king [[pangulu]] da reng kabundukang [[Himalayas]], a tubu ranglabuad deng lahing Tibetan. Maki ''average'' yang tas a 4,900 metru  16,000 pie), ing Tibet, at uli na niti, ya ing pekamatas a labuad king [[Yatu]]. Manibat kareng mengalabasan a decada, megi reng maralas ausang "[[Roof of the World]]" (Bubungan ning Yatu).<ref>[http://www.google.at/search?hl=en&q=Tibet+Roof+of+the+World&btnG=Google+Search e.g.Dieter Glogowski:] ''Tibet, Escape from the Roof of the World''<br />or [http://www.amazon.de/Trespassers-Roof-World-Exploration-Kodansha/dp/1568360509 Peter Hoykirk:] ''Trespassers on the Roof of the World: The Secret Exploration of Tibet''<br />or [http://www.tourism-watch.de/dt/23dt/23.hotel/index.html Tibet. Tourism Watch] Alec le Sueurs:''Running a Hotel on the Roof of the World - Five years in Tibet''<br /> or [http://www.spiegel.de/international/spiegel/0,1518,380808,00.html Spiegel Online]
''Tibet by Rail. By train on the roof of the world.''</ref>

King amlat ning Tibet, megi yang magsariling bangsa aniang milabas<ref>Beckwith, Christopher I. (1987): ''The Tibetan Empire in Central Asia: A History of the Struggle for Great Power among Tibetans, Turks, Arabs, and Chinese during the Early Middle Ages'', pp. 11-36. Princeton University Press. ISBN 0-691-02469-3.</ref>, mapipitna kareng miayaliwang kayarian, at aniang misan a panaun megi neng dake ning China. Ngeni, kayabe ya king [[Pangmaldang Republica ning China]] (PRC), kabang ating malating dake, agpang king kapamahalan ning PRC, ing [[kapamahalan ning Republica ning China, ampong mapilan pang aliwang bangsa, at mapilan pang grupung ala king kapamahalan (''non-government bodies'') o maki kaugnayan king pamagaral (''scholarly bodies''), tatalnan ne ning [[India]]. King salukuyan, e ya mikasundu ing kapamahalang PRC ampo ing [[:en:Central Tibetan Administration|Government of Tibet in Exile]] nung kapilan ya meging dake ning China ing Tibet, at nung makatalaruan ing pamangua ning China kng Tibet agpang king [[leying internacional]].<ref>[http://www.tibetjustice.org/reports/sovereignty/independent/d/index.html TIBET IS RIGHTFULLY AN INDEPENDENT STATE]</ref>   
Uling [[:en:Definitions of Tibet|ing bibilug king Tibet]] mapali yang pisasabian, e makanian kalagua o ka-simpli ing pakibaluan ya ing kayang dagul o populasiun, uling dakal lang grupung babandi kareng miayaliwang dake ning labuad antimong lugal a Tibetan. 

Minunang mika pamisanmetung king Tibet king lalam nang [[Songtsän Gampo]] kanitang kapitung dilanua o siglu. Ing kapamahalan da reng [[Dalai Lama]], a pamituki-tuki da reng pekapun a ispiritual, ing menibala king maragul a dake ning labuad ning Tibet dakal a pamitagun manibat aniang decadang 1640 angga king liban ne ning PRC aniang decadang 1950. King keraklan king panaun a iti, makalalam ya king [[:en:Qing Dynasty|Pamag-aring Qing]]. Metung yang sukad king upayang tatalnan da reng ''regent'' a atlu mukareng labing apat a Dalai Lama ing taganang menibala king Tibet, kabang king 77 porsientu ning panaun manibat aniang 1751 anggang 1960, deng ''regent'' ing taganang sasakup.<ref>Mullin, Glenn H. (2001). ''The Fourteen Dalai Lamas: A Sacred Legacy of Reincarnations'', pp. 47-49. Clear Light Publishers. Santa Fe, New Mexico. ISBN 1-57416-092-3.</ref> 
